ABC Institute of Technology - Student Handbook

About the College
ABC Institute of Technology was established in 2005. The college offers undergraduate and postgraduate programs in Computer Science, Information Technology, Artificial Intelligence, Mechanical Engineering, Civil Engineering, and Electronics Engineering. The campus is spread across 25 acres and includes modern laboratories, libraries, and sports facilities.

Library Information
The central library is open from 8:00 AM to 8:00 PM on weekdays. Students can borrow up to 4 books for a period of 14 days. Late returns incur a fine of Rs. 2 per day per book.

Attendance Policy
Students must maintain a minimum attendance of 75 percent in every course. Students with attendance below 75 percent may not be permitted to appear for the end-semester examination unless approved by the academic committee.

Examination Rules
Students must carry their college ID card during examinations. Mobile phones, smart watches, and electronic gadgets are not allowed inside the examination hall. Any form of malpractice will result in disciplinary action.

Hostel Facilities
The college provides separate hostel facilities for boys and girls. Hostel rooms are equipped with Wi-Fi, study tables, and common recreation areas. The hostel mess serves breakfast, lunch, snacks, and dinner.

Placement Cell
The Training and Placement Cell organizes aptitude training, technical workshops, and mock interviews. Top recruiters include Infosys, TCS, Wipro, Cognizant, and Accenture. The average annual package offered last year was 5.2 LPA.

Computer Science Department
The Computer Science Department offers courses in Data Structures, Algorithms, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Cloud Computing, and Cyber Security. The department has five computer laboratories with high-speed internet access.

Artificial Intelligence Club
The AI Club conducts workshops on Python, Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Generative AI, LangChain, Ollama, and Retrieval-Augmented Generation. Students participate in hackathons and industry projects.

Scholarships
Merit scholarships are awarded to students securing more than 85 percent marks in the previous academic year. Financial assistance is also available for economically disadvantaged students.

Sports and Cultural Activities
The college encourages students to participate in cricket, football, basketball, volleyball, athletics, music, dance, and drama events. Annual cultural festivals are organized every year.

Generative AI Course
The Generative AI One-Credit Course introduces students to Large Language Models, Prompt Engineering, Ollama, LangChain, ChromaDB, Retrieval-Augmented Generation, AI Agents, and Model Context Protocol. Students complete hands-on projects and mini assignments throughout the course.

Student Support Services
The Student Support Center provides academic counseling, career guidance, and mental wellness support. Students can contact the center between 9:00 AM and 5:00 PM on working days.
